title: For Sale:  Egyptian RASHEED Carbine - 7.62x39 Semi-Auto, Rare, Excellent
postcontent:
If you are looking at this listing then chances are you already know the story on this rifle.

It's quite rare with only 8000 ever made and of those about 2000 were imported into the USA. 

The Rasheed was based on the Swedish AG42b Ljungman rifle as was it's big brother the Hakim. 

These rifles are typically pretty beat up from the rough service they saw in Egypt. However this one is not, and it's in excellent condition. Metal and wood finish is 95% or better. Then the bore is bright and shiny. It's 100% mechanically as well. 

Make no mistake the Rasheed is equally capable to the SKS so it has a considerable amount of firepower. I've seen detachable 20 round mags for sale from time to time on GunBroker as well which would make this little rifle even more capable.

I believe it would be difficult to find a better Rasheed than what I'm offering here - especially one in original and not refinished condition.

Asking $795 FTF local sale only with pickup in the Brandon area. Buyer must be a Florida resident who is still least 18 years old.

Thanks for looking.

The Kel-Tec PLR-16 is a gas-operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in .223/5.56 NATO. The PLR (Pistol, Long Range) was designed for recreational target shooting, and small game, varmint, or predator hunting. title: For Sale:  Don't buy over priced guns, research 1st
postcontent:
www.cheaperthandirt.com
www.budsgunshop.com
www.palmettostatearmory.com

Check these websites before buying these over priced guns people want to list on here.  Just because they paid way too much for something means they try to sell you a now USED gun for way more than the gun goes on the open market BRAND NEW. 

SDVE about $300, KAHR CW about 315-340... etc.  People are asking way more than $100 over these prices for the same guns that have now been used.   Be smart and do some research.  Don't let these people inflate prices bc they bought something in a panic and paid way too much.

Buds lists FFL dealers in your area and show how much they charge.  Many can be found for $25 or so, depending on your location.  BUDS and Cheaperthandirt sell with free shipping on firearms.  Just because local gun stores try to sell KAHR products in the $500 range doesn't mean that's what you should pay, many can be hand brand new on websites for $350 range.  Local FFL transfers help support local business too and keep gun shops from gouging walk in customers.
